{"title_page": "2000\u201301 Kilmarnock F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n|club=[[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]]\n|season=[[2000\u201301 in Scottish football|2000-01 Season]]\n|manager= [[Bobby Williamson]]\n|chairman=\n|stadium=[[Rugby Park]]\n|league=[[Scottish Premier League]]\n|league result='''Fourth Place'''\n|cup1=[[Scottish Cup]]\n|cup1 result='''Quarter\u2013Final''', lost to [[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]]\n|cup2=[[Scottish League Cup]]\n|cup2 result='''Runners Up'''\n|league topscorer=<br />[[Paul Wright (footballer)|Paul Wright]] (8)\n|season topscorer=<br />[[Paul Wright (footballer)|Paul Wright]] (9)<br />[[Craig Dargo]] (9)\n|highest attendance=14,679 v [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]], [[Scottish Premier League|Premier League]], 5 August 2000 <!--LEAGUE ONLY-->\n|lowest attendance=6,018 v [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]], [[Scottish Premier League|Premier League]], 3 February 2001 <!--LEAGUE ONLY-->\n|average attendance=League: 8,224 \n|pattern_la1=_blue_stripes4\n|pattern_b1=_bluestripes4\n|pattern_ra1=_blue_stripes4\n|pattern_so1=_2bluestripes\n|leftarm1=\n|body1=\n|rightarm1=\n|shorts1=\n|socks1=\n|pattern_la2=\n|pattern_b2=_Roma2\n|pattern_ra2=\n|pattern_sh2=\n|pattern_so2=_color_3_stripes_black\n|leftarm2=333333\n|body2=333333\n|rightarm2=333333\n|shorts2=333333\n|socks2=\n|prevseason=[[1999\u20132000 Kilmarnock F.C. season|1999\u20132000]]\n|nextseason=[[2001\u201302 Kilmarnock F.C. season|2001\u201302]]\n}}\n\nThe [[2000\u201301 in Scottish football|2000\u201301 season]] was [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock's]] third consecutive season in the [[2000\u201301 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]]. Kilmarnock also competed in the [[2000\u201301 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]] and the [[2000\u201301 Scottish League Cup|Scottish League Cup]].\n\n\n\n==Summary==\n\n===Season===\n\nKilmarnock finished fourth in the [[2000\u201301 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]] with 54 points. They reached the final of the [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]] but were beaten by [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/cis_ins_cup/1228218.stm | title=Celtic 3-0 Kilmarnock | publisher=[[BBC]] | work=BBC Sport | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> They also reached the quarter\u2013final of the [[Scottish Cup]], losing to [[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.londonhearts.com/scores/a2000/kilmarnock2001.htm | title=Results for Kilmarnock for 2000\u201301 | publisher=londonhearts.com | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n\n''Kilmarnock's score comes first''\n\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#CCCCCC|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n\n===Scottish Premier League===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align:center\"\n!Match!!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|1||29 July 2000||[[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]||A||1\u20130||7,388||[[Gary Holt (footballer)|Holt]] 72'\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|2||5 August 2000||[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||H||2\u20134||14,679||[[Andy McLaren|McLaren]] 3', 10'\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|3||13 August 2000||[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]||A||1\u20132||58,054||[[Andy McLaren|McLaren]] 17'\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|4||16 August 2000||[[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]]||H||0\u20131||8,672||\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|5||19 August 2000||[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]||H||3\u20132||6,533||[[Craig Dargo|Dargo]] 26', [[Paul Wright (footballer)|Wright]] 76', [[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Dindeleux|Dindeleux]] 80'\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|6||26 August 2000||[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]||A||1\u20131||3,773||[[Andy McLaren|McLaren]] 13'\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|7||9 September 2000||[[